## Vercel Speed Insights Installation and Configuration

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js 16.1.6 project using the App Router.

### Changes Made:

**1. Package Installation:**
   - Installed `@vercel/speed-insights@^1.3.1` using npm
   - Updated package.json and package-lock.json with the new dependency

**2. Code Integration:**
   - Modified `src/app/layout.tsx`:
     - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
     - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the main content
     - Placed component after `</FinancialProfileProvider>` to ensure it loads after all page content

### Implementation Details:

Since this project uses:
- **Next.js 16.1.6** (well above the 13.5+ threshold)
- **App Router** architecture (confirmed by the presence of `src/app/layout.tsx`)

The implementation follows the recommended approach for modern Next.js:
- Used the `@vercel/speed-insights/next` import (optimized for App Router)
- Added the component directly to the root layout without needing a separate client component
- No `route` prop needed as the component automatically handles routing in App Router

### Verification:

✅ **Build Test:** Application builds successfully with no errors
✅ **Linting:** No new linting errors introduced (existing warnings are unrelated to this change)
✅ **Dependencies:** Lock files properly updated (package-lock.json)

### Files Modified:
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package and its dependencies
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component

The Speed Insights component is now properly integrated and will automatically track Core Web Vitals and performance metrics when the application is deployed to Vercel.
